{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-js","path":"/brief-generator/","result":{"data":{"prismicProject":{"uid":"brief-generator","id":"f82664c1-f8a0-5312-8307-6603ba994d7c","data":{"project_title":{"html":"<p>Brief Generator</p>","text":"Brief Generator"},"client":{"html":"<p>Self-Initiated</p>","text":"Self-Initiated"},"location":{"html":"<p>Glasgow, UK</p>","text":"Glasgow, UK"},"team":{"html":"<p>Theo Ford</p>","text":"Theo Ford"},"year":{"html":"<p>2016</p>","text":"2016"},"categories":[{"category":{"slug":"website","id":"ZMfW6RAAACMAPs1H"}},{"category":{"slug":"development","id":"ZMfW-BAAACMAPs2b"}}],"body1":[{"id":"text$c91d7e60-67c2-4a85-9a1a-a31ffffb9353","slice_type":"text","primary":{"text":{"html":"<p>Brief Generator began as a simple irreverent exercise to see whether I could automate my tutor. I created a generator tool that took a series of inputs derived from previous briefs from across the Glasgow School of Art. Each brief was broken into three categories: action, theme and tool, and I wrote an algorithm to randomise the combination of these variables. I took a user-centred approach in order to identify what method of brief generation was most effective, conducting user testing through workshops with my peers.</p>","text":"Brief Generator began as a simple irreverent exercise to see whether I could automate my tutor. I created a generator tool that took a series of inputs derived from previous briefs from across the Glasgow School of Art. Each brief was broken into three categories: action, theme and tool, and I wrote an algorithm to randomise the combination of these variables. I took a user-centred approach in order to identify what method of brief generation was most effective, conducting user testing through workshops with my peers."}}},{"id":"video$915226b1-2a5f-4791-9bc2-4d9ca43d35b2","slice_type":"video","primary":{"index_image":{"gatsbyImageData":{"images":{"sources":[{"srcSet":"https://images.prismic.io/theoford-1/90a2f3d1